Residents of Dutse community in Bwari area council have appealed to the minister of the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) Malam Muhammad Musa Bello, to construct a pedestrian bridge along the Dutse Market entrance, to allow for easy access to Dutse communities and the market. Some of the residents who spoke in a separate interview, lamented that since the construction work at the Dutse-Bwari express way begin, they have found it very difficult to access some areas, such as Dutsen-Alhaji First and Second Gates, as well as the market, from the opposite junction. A trader in the market, Mrs. Agnes Dauda, noted that crossing the road to the market has become a big challenge to pedestrians, adding that because of the improved state of the road, motorists now ply the road with recklessness. “It is very important for the minister to construct a pedestrian bridge at the junction of this market, because we that make use of the market do not find it easy to access the market at all. Whenever we want to cross to the market side, we are always scared, because of some reckless drivers who want to meet their targets for the day.” Also speaking, a resident of Dutsen-Alhaji community, Mr. Baba Simon, revealed that he almost knocked down by a fast-moving vehicle, while he was crossing the road. “If not for God that the vehicles coming were not on speed, I would have been a dead man by now. With the present state of this road, it has become a dead trap to many pedestrians who access the market or go into the other side of Dutsen-Alhaji community. “If the minister wants to avert any future deaths by accident on this market road, he should please construct a pedestrians bridge here at the market, before the road is completed, so that people can have access to the market and the other side of Dutse communities,” he said.